# DCA OS v2 safety

- Before material work, read the canonical authority chain in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/README.md`.
- Phase 1 is complete and must not be reopened. Phase 2 runtime is `NOT_STARTED`; only the offline P2-A foundation and disabled owner-run exporter are implemented.
- Do not inspect `.env` files or secrets. Do not perform production/VPS, remote database/staging, live integration, cost-incurring, destructive migration, legal/privacy issues, actual snapshot, backfill, reconciliation, switch, cleanup, unresolved critical/canonical conflicts, or Tellanic actions unless explicitly owner-authorized.
- Do not run Docker, access a database, or execute the exporter without explicit owner authorization.
- Use one executor per task area. Do not make concurrent Cursor and Codex edits to the same scope.
- Commits, pushes, PRs, and agents are allowed only when an explicit assigned mission authorizes them.
- Use PowerShell on Windows and Bash in WSL/Linux.
